# Frontend Engineering Rules

## Tools and Frameworks

- React 19, TypeScript, Vite, TanStack Query, Tailwind CSS
- Single-page dashboard only — no routing beyond the main view

## Core Principles

- Prioritize clarity for a busy engineering leader: scores must be understandable at a glance.
- Every score shown in the UI must include its definition and interpretation (from the API or shared types).
- Prefer a working, readable MVP over polish; fit the entire dashboard on one laptop screen without scrolling the page.

## Dashboard Layout

- Page title at the top.
- Four tabs: **Overall** (weighted combination of category scores), **Quantity**, **Quality**, **Collaboration**.
- Each tab contains:
  - A brief category description (definition + how to read the score).
  - A leaderboard: top 5 contributors for that view, plus one **Average** row at the bottom.
  - A breakdown section: each sub-metric with its own description and mini-leaderboard (top 5 + average).

## Data Fetching and States

- Use TanStack Query for all server data.
- Show a loading state while metrics are fetching.
- Show a clear, actionable error message when loading fails (do not fail silently).

## Code Quality

- Use TypeScript strictly; type API responses and component props.
- Keep components small and focused; match existing patterns before adding abstractions.
- Use Tailwind for styling; keep layout compact for the single-page constraint.
